      • INVALID_ID

        public static final long INVALID_ID

    • Constructor Detail

      • Student

        public Student()
        Create an empty student object. The ID of the student will be set to INVALID_ID.

        Note that upon construction, this Student object is not valid for insertion into the database. The name of the student must be set for the student to insertable into the database.

      • setID

        public Student setID(long id)
        Sets the unique ID of the student to the given value.

        NOTE: this method should ONLY be called by the StudentManager class! This ID represents the unique ID of the student in the underlying database, and should not be changed by other classes.

        Parameters:
        id - the ID to set
        Returns:
        this, for chaining

      • getImgName

        public String getImgName()
        Gets the name of the image of this student, if there is one. The image itself is stored in an external file that is private to this app.
        Returns:
        the name of the image associated with the student (if it exists); otherwise null

      • setImgName

        public Student setImgName(String imgName)
